<section class="section series-intro">
  <div class="series-intro-card reveal">
    <div class="series-intro-content">
      <h2>Two Networks. 3,200 Years. One Question.</h2>
      <p class="series-intro-lead">
        Can civilizational collapse be prevented through knowledge distribution—or is it inevitable,
        requiring genetic engineering of optimal survivors?
      </p>
      <div class="networks-grid">
        <div class="network-card">
          <h3>The Genesis Protocol</h3>
          <p class="network-label">Defensive Network</p>
          <p>Founded 1177 BCE by Egyptian scribe Nefertari. Philosophy: "Collapse is PREVENTABLE
          through pattern recognition." Strategy: Distribute knowledge freely, teach methodology
          to everyone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="network-card">
          <h3>The Order</h3>
          <p class="network-label">Offensive Network</p>
          <p>Founded 1177 BCE by Amenhotep. Philosophy: "Collapse is INEVITABLE—engineer who survives."
          Strategy: Centralized control, selective breeding programs, genetic optimization.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="series-tagline">
        Neither side is evil. Both genuinely believe they're saving humanity.
        The 3,200-year moral ambiguity is the point.
      </p>
      <a class="button outline" href="/series/">Explore the complete saga</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="books" class="section books">
  <div class="section-header reveal">
    <h2>Featured Books</h2>
